        "body": "## Summary\n\n- hardens plugin-owned schema and metadata boundaries found during fuzzing with synthetic `fuzzplugin` / `mockplugin` fixtures\n- latest refresh hardens channel plugin Gateway method discovery: advertised method lists, startup/reload method advertisement, and web-login provider selection now project channel `gatewayMethods` / `gatewayMethodDescriptors` through bounded reads\n- keeps the draft PR branch updated as work continues; current head is `b3d349a3a72117f03e2ae47582524f2b358443cc`, proven on `origin/main` at `7b3104fe4c1f3daee57ac31ff81136f595896200`\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check src/gateway/channel-gateway-methods.ts src/gateway/server.impl.ts src/gateway/server-methods-list.ts src/gateway/server-methods-list.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/web.ts src/gateway/server-methods/web.start.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD -- src/gateway/channel-gateway-methods.ts src/gateway/server.impl.ts src/gateway/server-methods-list.ts src/gateway/server-methods-list.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/web.ts src/gateway/server-methods/web.start.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/gateway/channel-gateway-methods.ts src/gateway/server.impl.ts src/gateway/server-methods-list.ts src/gateway/server-methods-list.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/web.ts src/gateway/server-methods/web.start.test.ts`\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/gateway/server-methods-list.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/web.start.test.ts --reporter=verbose`: 2 files passed, 11 tests passed\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`: clean on the channel Gateway method discovery slice after fixing the startup advertisement path and indexed-array getter edge found by review\n- scrubbed diff/spec/PR body for the reported plugin name and private local paths\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: plugin-owned schema, metadata, command metadata, hook registration, tool registration options, CLI registration options, bundled agent tool result middleware options, captured middleware options, captured capability id surfaces, memory embedding provider registration, runtime embedding adapter merge/direct lookup, process-global embedding provider registry restore/list/register paths, migration provider runtime resolution, provider contract registry resolution, setup-only provider/backend runtime registration, compaction provider registration, capability provider runtime resolution, provider runtime hook lookup, shared provider resolver projection, active runtime CLI backend projection, provider discovery entry projection, explicit web provider public artifact projection, document/web-content extractor public artifact projection, trusted tool policy decision handling, Gateway Control UI descriptor projection, Gateway plugin session action dispatch, dynamic plugin session action method-scope resolution, plugin-registered Gateway method descriptor scope resolution, and channel plugin Gateway method discovery no longer trust crashy getters, revoked proxies, mutable arrays/records, malformed runtime entries, malformed ids, unreadable aliases, unreadable hook aliases, unreadable labels/auth fields, unreadable backend configs, unreadable CLI commands, hostile callback metadata, throwing provider/extractor factories, unreadable public artifact metadata, throwing trusted policy evaluators, unreadable trusted policy decision fields, unreadable gateway descriptor metadata, unreadable session action metadata, malformed matched action scopes, unreadable gateway method descriptor names/scopes, unreadable channel gateway method arrays, unreadable channel gateway method array elements, or unreadable channel gateway method descriptor names while healthy sibling registrations continue where the surface is availability-oriented and security-sensitive policy/scope failures fail closed.\n\nReal environment tested: local linked OpenClaw worktree on the draft PR branch, rebased onto `origin/main` at `7b3104fe4c1f3daee57ac31ff81136f595896200`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: ran focused formatting, diff check, linting, Vitest, and autoreview commands listed in Verification after the channel Gateway method discovery slice; after the final rebase, reran formatting, diff check, linting, and Vitest on the rebased head.\n\nEvidence after fix: gateway method-list tests now cover unreadable `fuzzplugin` channel gateway method array elements, unreadable `fuzzplugin` descriptor array elements, unreadable descriptor names, and preservation of a healthy `mockplugin.gateway.inspect` descriptor. Web login tests now cover the same malformed channel method discovery inputs while still selecting and invoking a healthy `mockplugin` login provider. The startup/reload method advertisement path uses the same bounded projection helper.\n\nObserved result after fix: malformed channel plugin Gateway method metadata no longer crashes advertised method listing, startup/reload method advertisement, or web-login provider discovery; healthy sibling Gateway methods and login providers still work.\n\nWhat was not tested: broad Blacksmith/Testbox changed gate and AWS Crabbox broad gate were not rerun for this refresh; current proof is the targeted channel/Gateway method discovery fuzz surface plus formatter/lint/autoreview checks.\n",
